alls `stagedFilesOverlapWithContent()` (lines 173-326 in `content_overlap.go`)\\n   - Cost: worktree.Status() + index access + blob comparisons\\n\\n### Performance Characteristics:\\n- **Shadow branch lookup**: Fast (git ref cache)\\n- **Tree operations**: Moderate (git object store)\\n- **Transcript parsing**: **SLOW** - parses entire transcript regardless of what was last condensed\\n  - No incremental tracking; always counts full lines/messages\\n  - For large sessions, this is the dominant cost\\n- **Content overlap check**: Moderate-to-slow depending on staged file count and sizes\\n  - Requires git index access and potentially blob reading for new files\\n  - `hasSignificantContentOverlap()` parses file contents to extract lines\\n\\n---\\n\\n## **Scenario 2: Shadow Branch Without Transcript (Carry-Forward)**\\n\\n**Code Path:** Lines 1006-1030 in `manual_commit_hooks.go`\\n\\n### What happens:\\n1. **Shadow branch exists but no transcript file** (line 1008)\\n   - Shadow tree is already loaded from Scenario 1 attempt\\n   - No transcript parsing needed\\n\\n2. **Check FilesTouched** (lines 1009-1030):\\n   - If `state.FilesTouched` has files, assume new content\\n   - Return quickly with overlay check\\n\\n3. **Staged files overlap check** (lines 1012-1022):\\n   - `getStagedFiles()` - call worktree.Status() to get staging area\\n   - `stagedFilesOverlapWithContent()` - content-aware comparison\\n   - Cost: worktree.Status() + tree lookups + blob operations for new files\\n\\n4. **Fallback to live transcript** (lines 1032-1036):\\n   - If no staged files and no FilesTouched, fall through to live transcript check\\n\\n### Performance Characteristics:\\n- **Shadow branch exists**: Already loaded, minimal overhead\\n- **Skips transcript parsing**: Fast path!\\n- **Staged file check**: Moderate (worktree.Status() is relatively fast)\\n- **Content overlap**: Can be expensive for new files (blob reading)\\n- **Overall**: Much faster than Scenario 1 if no staged files exist\\n\\n---\\n\\n## **Scenario 3: No Shadow Branch (Live Transcript)**\\n\\n**Code Path:** Lines 1101-1133 in `manual_commit_hooks.go`\\n\\n### What happens:\\n1. **Shadow branch missing** (line 967 - error path)\\n   - Indicates no Stop/SaveStep happened yet, agent is mid-turn\\n\\n2. **Extract from live transcript** (line 976):\\n   - `extractNewModifiedFilesFromLiveTranscript()` (lines 1147-1179)\\n   - Get agent analyzer for transcript type\\n   - `analyzer.GetTranscriptPosition()` - check if transcript grew\\n   - Cost: Agent-specific implementation (for Claude Code: fast line count)\\n\\n3. **Modified files extraction** (lines 1184-1254):\\n   - For Claude Code: `claudecode.ExtractAllModifiedFiles()` (line 1207)\\n     - Parses main transcript AND subagent transcripts\\n     - Extracts tool_use entries with file paths\\n     - **EXPENSIVE** - full transcript parse with regex/JSON parsing\\n   - Normalizes paths to repo-relative format\\n\\n4. **Staged files comparison** (lines 1117-1130):\\n   - `getStagedFiles()` - worktree.Status()\\n   - `hasOverlappingFiles()` - simple filename intersection check (lines 330-342)\\n   - Cost: Moderate (no content-aware comparison, just names)\\n\\n### Performance Characteristics:\\n- **Shadow branch lookup**: Fast (fails quickly)\\n- **Transcript extraction**: **EXPENSIVE**\\n  - Reads live transcript from disk (os.ReadFile)\\n  - Claude Code extracts ALL modified files from main + subagent transcripts\\n  - Includes regex/JSON parsing for tool_use entries\\n  - Normalizes paths (potential string allocations)\\n- **File overlap check**: Fast (simple filename matching, no content check)\\n- **Overall**: Can be quite slow for large sessions with many subagent turns\\n  - But simpler overlap detection makes it acceptable for mid-session commits\\n\\n---\\n\\n## **Helper Function Performance Analysis**\\n\\n### `getStagedFiles()` (lines 1615-1634)\\n```go\\n- worktree.Status() → go-git scans index vs worktree\\n- Iterates through all status entries, filters by Staging status\\n- Cost: O(files in index) - linear but typically fast for practical repos\\n```\\n\\n### `stagedFilesOverlapWithContent()` (lines 173-326 in `content_overlap.go`)\\n```\\n1. repo.Head() - fast git ref lookup\\n2. repo.CommitObject() - git object lookup\\n3. repo.Storer.Index() - load index into memory (single operation, O(1))\\n4. Loop through staged files:\\n   - headTree.File(path) - tree entry lookup, O(log n)\\n   - shadowTree.File(path) - tree entry lookup, O(log n)\\n   - For new files with mismatched hashes:\\n     - repo.BlobObject(hash) - object store lookup\\n     - Read blob contents (io.ReadAll) - **CAN BE EXPENSIVE** for large files\\n     - hasSignificantContentOverlap() - parses both files into lines\\n       - extractSignificantLines() - builds set of lines >= 10 chars\\n       - Line-by-line comparison, O(n*m) worst case\\n\\nCost: O(staged_files * avg_blob_size) for new file content checks\\n```\\n\\n### `countTranscriptItems()` (lines 499-524)\\n```go\\n- For Claude Code (JSONL):\\n  - strings.Split(content, \\\"\\\\n\\\") → O(file_size)\\n  - Count lines after filtering empty ones\\n  - Cost: Full file scan, no incremental tracking\\n  \\n- For Gemini (JSON):\\n  - geminicli.ParseTranscript() - full JSON parse\\n  - Cost: O(file_size) with overhead\\n```\\n\\n---\\n\\n## **Key Findings & Bottlenecks**\\n\\n| Operation | Scenario 1 | Scenario 2 | Scenario 3 | Cost |\\n|-----------|-----------|-----------|-----------|------|\\n| Shadow branch lookup | ✓ | ✓ | ✗ | O(1) / Fast miss |\\n| Transcript parsing | **✓ SLOW** | - | ✓ SLOW | O(n) full file |\\n| Staged files check | ✓ | ✓ | ✓ | O(m) where m=staged files |\\n| Content overlap (new files) | ✓ | ✓ | - | O(size) blob reads |\\n| Subagent parsing | - | - | **✓ SLOW** | O(n) per subagent |\\n\\n### **The Main Performance Hotspot: Transcript Counting**\\n- `countTranscriptItems()` always parses the **entire transcript** regardless of positio