ipt()` → `getStagedFiles()` → `hasOverlappingFiles()`\\n- Expected bottleneck: live transcript parsing + worktree.Status()\\n\\n## Available Infrastructure\\n\\nThe `benchutil` package (`cmd/entire/cli/benchutil/`) provides:\\n- `NewBenchRepo(b, RepoOpts)` - creates git repo with files and commits\\n- `CreateSessionState(b, SessionOpts)` - creates session state file in `.git/entire-sessions/`\\n- `SeedShadowBranch(b, sessionID, checkpointCount, filesPerCheckpoint)` - creates shadow branch with checkpoints (transcript + metadata)\\n- `GenerateTranscript(TranscriptOpts)` - generates realistic JSONL transcript data\\n- `WriteTranscriptFile(b, sessionID, data)` - writes transcript to `.entire/tmp/`\\n- `WriteFile(b, relPath, content)` + `AddAndCommit(b, msg, files...)` - file operations\\n\\nThe `SessionOpts` struct supports: `SessionID`, `Phase`, `StepCount`, `FilesTouched`, `TranscriptPath`, `AgentType`.\\n\\n### Key details for setup:\\n\\n1. For Scenario 1 (shadow branch with transcript): Use `SeedShadowBranch()` which creates shadow branch with transcript data. Set session phase to IDLE.\\n\\n2. For Scenario 2 (shadow branch without transcript): Need to create a shadow branch that has file content but NO transcript file. This mimics carry-forward. `SeedShadowBranch` creates transcripts, so we may need a different approach — perhaps manually creating the shadow branch with only file blobs, or using the `checkpoint.WriteTemporary` with empty MetadataDir (which is what `carryForwardToNewShadowBranch` does).\\n\\n3. For Scenario 3 (no shadow branch, live transcript): Don't create any shadow branch. Write a live transcript file to disk using `WriteTranscriptFile`. Set session phase to ACTIVE.\\n\\nFor all scenarios, we need staged files that overlap with the session's files to trigger the full code path.\\n\\n## Design Requirements\\n\\n- Create a single benchmark file, e.g. `cmd/entire/cli/strategy/prepare_commit_msg_bench_test.go`\\n- Each scenario should be a sub-ben