RepoOpts{FileCount: N})`\\n2. `CreateSessionState(b, SessionOpts{Phase: session.PhaseIdle, FilesTouched: files})`\\n3. Use `Store.WriteTemporary()` with empty `MetadataDir`/`MetadataDirAbs` (mimics `carryForwardToNewShadowBranch`)\\n4. Modify + stage overlapping files\\n\\n### Scenario 3: No shadow branch (live transcript, mid-turn)\\n\\nAgent is still running, no shadow branch yet. Falls through to live transcript parsing.\\n\\n**Code path**: shadow branch ref miss → `sessionHasNewContentFromLiveTranscript()` → `ExtractAllModifiedFiles()` from disk → `getStagedFiles()` → `hasOverlappingFiles()`\\n\\n**Setup**:\\n1. `NewBenchRepo(b, RepoOpts{FileCount: N})`\\n2. Write Claude Code format transcript to disk via `WriteTranscriptFile()`\\n3. `CreateSessionState(b, SessionOpts{Phase: session.PhaseActive, TranscriptPath: path})`\\n4. Do NOT create any shadow branch\\n5. Modify + stage overlapping files\\n\\n**Transcript format**: Must use Claude Code nested JSONL (`type: \\\"assistant\\\"`, `message.content[].type: \\\"tool_use\\\"`, `message.content[].name: \\\"Write\\\"`, `message.content[].input.file_path: \\\"/abs/path\\\"`). Use the same structure as `makeWriteToolLine` in `cmd/entire/cli/agent/claudecode/transcript_test.go`.\\n\\n## Benchmark Parameters\\n\\n```go\\nvar benchCases = []struct {\\n    name            string\\n    transcriptLines int\\n    fileCount       int\\n}{\\n    {\\\"Small_20msg_3files\\\", 20, 3},\\n    {\\\"Medium_200msg_10files\\\", 200, 10},\\n    {\\\"Large_2000msg_30files\\\", 2000, 30},\\n}\\n```\\n\\n## Helper Functions (local to bench file)\\n\\n1. **`seedShadowWithTranscript(b, br, sessionID, files, transcriptLines)`** — creates shadow branch with transcript of specified size using `Store.WriteTemporary` + generated transcript in metadata dir\\n2. **`seedShadowCarryForward(b, br, sessionID, files)`** — creates shadow branch with only file content (no metadata dir)\\n3. **`generateClaudeTranscriptJSONL(repoDir string, files []string, lines int) []byte`** — generates Claude Code format JSONL with Write tool_use entries using absolute paths\\n4. **`stageOverlappingFiles(b, br, files)`** — modifies and stages files to trigger overlap detection\\n\\n## Benchmark Structure\\n\\n```go\\nfunc BenchmarkSessionHasNewContent(b *testing.B) {\\n    b.Run(\\\"ShadowWithTranscript\\\", func(b *testing.B) {\\n        for _, tc := range benchCases {\\n            b.Run(tc.name, func(b *testing.B) {\\n                // setup ...\\n                s := &ManualCommitStrategy{}\\n                b.ResetTimer()\\n                for b.Loop() {\\n                    s.sessionHasNewContent(repo, state)\\n                }\\n            })\\n        }\\n    })\\n    b.Run(\\\"ShadowCarryForward\\\", func(b *testing.B) { ... })\\n    b.Run(\\\"LiveTranscript\\\", func(b *testing.B) { ... })\\n}\\n```\\n\\n## Key Details\\n\\n- **No `os.Chdir` needed**: `sessionHasNewContent` takes `*git.Repository` directly. `getStagedFiles` works via the repo object. Scenario 3 uses `state.WorktreePath` (set by `CreateSessionState`), so path normalization works without chdir.\\n- **Import `_ \\\"github.com/entireio/cli/cmd/entire/cli/agent/claudecode\\\"`**: Scenario 3 calls `agent.GetByAgentType()` which requires the Claude Code agent to be registered.\\n- **`&ManualCommitStrategy{}`** is sufficient: `sessionHasNewContent` doesn't use the strategy's lazy-init fields (stateStore, checkpointStore).\\n- **Staging is stable across iterations**: files staged once in setup, never committed, so `worktree.Status()` returns consistent results.\\n\\n## Verification\\n\\n```bash\\ngo test -bench=BenchmarkSessionHasNewContent -benchmem -count=3 ./cmd/entire/cli/strategy/...\\n```\\n\\nCheck that:\\n1. All 3 scenarios run without errors\\n2. Timing differences between scenarios are visible\\n3. Large transcript cases show measurable overhead vs small ones\\n\"},\"caller\":{\"type\":\"direct\"}}],\"stop_reason\":null,\"stop_sequence\":null,\"usage\