table across iterations**: files staged once in setup, never committed, so `worktree.Status()` returns consistent results.\\n\\n## Verification\\n\\n```bash\\ngo test -bench=BenchmarkSessionHasNewContent -benchmem -count=3 ./cmd/entire/cli/strategy/...\\n```\\n\\nCheck that:\\n1. All 3 scenarios run without errors\\n2. Timing differences between scenarios are visible\\n3. Large transcript cases show measurable overhead vs small ones\\n\",\"structuredPatch\":[{\"oldStart\":1,\"oldLines\":36,\"newStart\":1,\"newLines\":114,\"lines\":[\"-# Add Debug Timing Logs to Git Hooks\",\"+# Benchmark: PrepareCommitMsg Performance Scenarios\",\" \",\" ## Context\",\" \",\"-Performance testing of the prepare-commit-msg hook. Need visibility into how long the main hook methods take.\",\"+Performance testing showed session state loading (~1s for 100x4MB files) is not the main bottleneck. Need to isolate and measure the 3 distinct code paths inside `sessionHasNewContent` to find what else is slow.\",\" \",\" ## Approach\",\" \",\"-Add `logging.LogDuration` calls at the top of each main hook method using `defer`, so the total time of each method is logged at `DEBUG` level.\",\"+Create a single Go benchmark file with 3 sub-benchmarks, each setting up a realistic repo that triggers a specific `sessionHasNewContent` code path. Vary transcript size and file count per scenario.\",\" \",\"-## Files to Modify\",\"+## File to Create\",\" \",\"-### 1. `cmd/entire/cli/strategy/manual_commit_hooks.go`\",\"+**`cmd/entire/cli/strategy/prepare_commit_msg_bench_test.go`** (package `strategy` — needs unexported access to `sessionHasNewContent`)\",\" \",\"-Add `defer logging.LogDuration(...)` at the top of:\",\"-- `PrepareCommitMsg()` (line 234)\",\"-- `handleAmendCommitMsg()` (line 393)\",\"-- `CommitMsg()` (line 125)\",\"-- `PostCommit()` (line 602)\",\"+## Scenarios\",\" \",\"-## Pattern\",\"+### Scenario 1: Shadow branch WITH transcript (idle session)\",\" \",\"+The normal path when a human commit