tire/cli/strategy/manual_commit_hooks.go`\\n\\nAdd `defer logging.LogDuration(...)` at the top of:\\n- `PrepareCommitMsg()` (line 234)\\n- `handleAmendCommitMsg()` (line 393)\\n- `CommitMsg()` (line 125)\\n- `PostCommit()` (line 602)\\n\\n## Pattern\\n\\n```go\\nfunc (s *ManualCommitStrategy) PrepareCommitMsg(...) error {\\n    start := time.Now()\\n    defer logging.LogDuration(logCtx, slog.LevelDebug, \\\"PrepareCommitMsg total\\\", start)\\n    // ... rest unchanged\\n}\\n```\\n\\n## Verification\\n\\n1. Set `ENTIRE_LOG_LEVEL=DEBUG`\\n2. Make a commit in a repo with an active session\\n3. Check `.entire/logs/entire.log` for timing entries\\n4. `mise run fmt && mise run lint && mise run test:ci`\\n\"},\"sourceToolAssistantUUID\":\"b3fc913b-1188-4fbd-a585-18b681b8c31a\"}\n{\"parentUuid\":\"626059ec-933c-4711-8180-f72a86ad4b36\",\"isSidechain\":false,\"userType\":\"external\",\"cwd\":\"/Users/gtrrz-victor/wks/cli/remove-auto-commit\",\"sessionId\":\"d1edaaf5-0e56-4080-8ccf-d4691be6ffc9\",\"version\":\"2.1.50\",\"gitBranch\":\"gtrrz-victor/pre-commit-performance\",\"slug\":\"enchanted-weaving-newt\",\"message\":{\"model\":\"claude-opus-4-6\",\"id\":\"msg_01CXCnmSF9gzwnfDp6NPqwhj\",\"type\":\"message\",\"role\":\"assistant\",\"content\":[{\"type\":\"tool_use\",\"id\":\"toolu_01TiQtkrrepA5VsUocMzAjjR\",\"name\":\"ExitPlanMode\",\"input\":{\"plan\":\"# Benchmark: PrepareCommitMsg Performance Scenarios\\n\\n## Context\\n\\nPerformance testing showed session state loading (~1s for 100x4MB files) is not the main bottleneck. Need to isolate and measure the 3 distinct code paths inside `sessionHasNewContent` to find what else is slow.\\n\\n## Approach\\n\\nCreate a single Go benchmark file with 3 sub-benchmarks, each setting up a realistic repo that triggers a specific `sessionHasNewContent` code path. Vary transcript size and file count per scenario.\\n\\n## File to Create\\n\\n**`cmd/entire/cli/strategy/prepare_commit_msg_bench_test.go`** (package `strategy` — needs unexported access to `sessionHasNewContent`)\\n\\n## Scenarios\\n\\n### Scenario 1: Shadow branch WITH transcript (idle session)\\n\\nThe normal path when a human commits after the agent stopped.\\n\\n**Code path**: shadow branch ref → commit/tree → read transcript blob → `countTranscriptItems()` → `getStagedFiles()` → `stagedFilesOverlapWithContent()`\\n\\n**Setup**:\\n1. `NewBenchRepo(b, RepoOpts{FileCount: N})` — creates repo with N tracked files\\n2. `CreateSessionState(b, SessionOpts{Phase: session.PhaseIdle, FilesTouched: files})` — idle session\\n3. Use `Store.WriteTemporary()` with a metadata dir containing a transcript of the desired size (NOT `SeedShadowBranch` which hardcodes 5-message transcripts)\\n4. Modify + stage overlapping files via `wt.Add()`\\n\\n### Scenario 2: Shadow branch WITHOUT transcript (carry-forward)\\n\\nAfter a mid-session commit, remaining files are carried forward to a new shadow branch with no transcript.\\n\\n**Code path**: shadow branch ref → commit/tree → no transcript → check `FilesTouched` → `getStagedFiles()` → `stagedFilesOverlapWithContent()`\\n\\n**Setup**:\\n1. `NewBenchRepo(b, RepoOpts{FileCount: N})`\\n2. `CreateSessionState(b, SessionOpts{Phase: session.PhaseIdle, FilesTouched: files})`\\n3. Use `Store.WriteTemporary()` with empty `MetadataDir`/`MetadataDirAbs` (mimics `carryForwardToNewShadowBranch`)\\n4. Modify + stage overlapping files\\n\\n### Scenario 3: No shadow branch (live transcript, mid-turn)\\n\\nAgent is still running, no shadow branch yet. Falls through to live transcript parsing.\\n\\n**Code path**: shadow branch ref miss → `sessionHasNewContentFromLiveTranscript()` → `ExtractAllModifiedFiles()` from disk → `getStagedFiles()` → `hasOverlappingFiles()`\\n\\n**Setup**:\\n1. `NewBenchRepo(b, RepoOpts{FileCount: N})`\\n2. Write Claude Code format transcript to disk via `WriteTranscriptFile()`\\n3. `CreateSessionState(b, SessionOpts{Phase: session.PhaseActive, TranscriptPath: path})`\\n4. Do NOT create any shadow branch\\n5. Modify + stage overlapping files\\n\\n**Transcript format**: Must use Claude Code nested JSONL (`type: \\\"assistant\\\"`, `message.content[].type: \\\"tool_use\\\"`, `message.content[].name: \\\"Write\\\"`, `message.content[].input.file_path: \\\"/abs/path\\\"`). Use the same structure as `makeWriteToolLine` in `cmd/entire/cli/agent/claudecode/transcript_test.go`.\\n\\n## Benchmark Parameters\\n\\n```go\\nvar benchCases = []struct {\\n    name            string\\n    transcriptLines int\\n    fileCount       int\\n}{\\n    {\\\"Small_20msg_3files\\\", 20, 3},\\n    {\\\"Medium_200msg_10files\\\", 200, 10},\\n    {\\\"Large_2000msg_30files\\\", 2000, 30},\\n}\\n```\\n\\n## Helper Functions (local to bench file)\\n\\n1. **`seedShadowWithTranscript(b, br, sessionID, files, transcriptLines)`** — creates shadow branch with transcript of specified size using `Store.WriteTemporary` + generated transcript in metadata dir\\n2. **`seedShadowCarryForward(b, br, sessionID, files)`** — creates shadow branch with only file content (no metadata dir)\\n3. **`generateClaudeTranscriptJSONL(repoDir string, files []string, lines int) []byte`** — generates Claude Code format JSONL with Write tool_use entries using absolute paths\\n4. **`stageOverlappingFiles(b, br, files)`** — modifies and stages files to trigger overlap detection\\n\\n## Benchmark Structure\\n\\n```go\\nfunc BenchmarkSessionHasNewContent(b *testing.B) {\\n    b.Run(\\\"ShadowWithTranscript\\\", func(b *testing.B) {\\n        for _, tc := range benchCases {\\n            b.Run(tc.name, func(b *testing.B) {\\n                // setup ...\\n                s := &ManualCommitStrategy{}\\n                b.ResetTimer()\\n                for b.Loop() {\\n                    s.sessionHasNewContent(repo, state)\\n                }\\n            })\\n        }\\n    })\\n    b.Run(\\\"ShadowCarryForward\\\", func(b *testing.B) { ... })\\n    b.Run(\\\"LiveTranscript\\\", func(b *testing.B) { ... })\\n}\\n```\\n\\n## Key Details\\n\\n- **No `os.Chdir` needed**: `sessionHasNewContent` takes `*git.Repository` directly. `getStagedFiles` works via the repo object. Scenario 3 uses `state.WorktreePath` (set by `CreateSessionState`), so path normalization works without chdir.\\n- **Import `_ \\\"github.com/entireio/cli/cmd/entire/cli/agent/claudecode\\\"`**: Scenario 3 calls `agent.GetByAgentType()` which requires the Claude Code agent to be registered.\\n- **`&ManualCommitStrategy{}`** is sufficient: `sessionHasNewContent` doesn't use the strategy's lazy-init fields (stateStore, checkpointStore).\\n- **Staging is stable across iterations**: files staged once in setup, never committed, so `worktree.Status()` returns consistent results.\\n\\n## Verification\\n\\n```bash\\ngo test -bench=BenchmarkSessionHasNewContent -benchmem -count=3 ./cmd/entire/cli/strategy/...\\n```\\n\\nCheck that:\\n1. All 3 scenarios run without errors\\n2. Timing differences between scenarios are visible\\n3. Large transcript cases show measurable overhead vs small ones\\n\"},\"caller\":{\"type\":\"direct\"}}],\"stop_reason\":null,\"stop_sequence\":null,\"usage\":{\"input_tokens\":1,\"cache_creation_input_tokens\":1829,\"cache_read_input_tokens\":146766,\"cache_creation\":{\"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens\":0,\"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens\":1829},\"output_tokens\":22,\"service_tier\":\"standard\",\"inference_geo\":\"not_available\"}},\"requestId\":\"req_011CYQT4LDRusZkvQZWzQFPC\",\"type\":\"assistant\",\"uuid\":\"65a304ca-114b-4ee3-b01b-ef367db85c3f\",\"timestamp\":\"2026-02-23T05:29:37.315Z\"}\n{\"type\":\"queue-operation\",\"operation\":\"remove\",\"timestamp\":\"2026-02-23T05:31:49.851Z\",\"sessionId\":\"d1edaaf5-0e56-4080-8ccf-d4691be6ffc9\"}\n{\"type\":\"queue-operation\",\"operation\":\"remove\",\"timestamp\":\"2026-02-23T05:31:49.851Z\",\"sessionId\":\"d1edaaf5-0e56-4080-8ccf-d4691be6ffc9\"}\n{\"type\":\"queue-operation\",\"operation\":\"remove\",\"timestamp\":\"2026-02-23T05:31:49.851Z\",\"sessionId\":\"d1edaa